article.headline: Xavier 69, Lehigh 63
article.story: CINCINNATI (AP) -- Josh Duncan scored 14 points to help Xavier snap a three-game losing streak, and the Musketeers beat Lehigh 69-63 Tuesday night. Justin Cage added 12 points for Xavier (3-4), Brian Thornton 11 and Dedrick Finn 10. Nick Monserez led Lehigh (4-6) with 20 points, and Joe Knight added 14. Xavier led comfortably most of the game but Monserez and Knight helped Lehigh close to within four points with 1:43 left. The Musketeers led by 14 with 4:50 to play when Knight drove the lane to key a 9-1 run. Monserez hit a free throw and assisted on Knight's 3-pointer, then found Jose Olivero for a 3-point goal to cap the drive. The win let Xavier avoid its first four-game losing streak at home since the 1981-82 season. Three straight losses to Miami of Ohio, Creighton and Mississippi State are the only losses to non-league opponents in the five-year history of the Cintas Center.
